Language name: Angas
Language number: 4367
Alternate names: 
Classification: Afro-Asiatic, Chadic
Comments: Angas has 3 level tones.  Burquest reports many 
consonants with a labialized offglide.  These are treated 
as Cw clusters.  Palatalization only occurs with bilabials 
and, under an analysis which treats the palatals as 
palatalized velars, with velars and is treated as a 
segmental feature.

Sources: 
Burquest, D.A. 1971. A Preliminary Study of Angas 
Phonology. Institute of Linguistics, Zaria.